td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fact is...</span><hr size=1> I continue to have a great deal of fun playing EQ.<br>
<br>
However, I think the game is broken, it is just still fun to play.  Here is why it is broken:<br>
<br>
They raised the level cap. VI designed a game, designed spells, designed skills, and designed mobs around a player base that had skill levels from 1 to 50.  When they raised players levels to 60, suddenly there were a great many problems with virtually every class as a result.  <br>
<br>
Epic mobs:  *sigh*  As someone once said, the only thing epic is the wait.  however, when they instituted the 'epic' quests, they put the mobs in the planes, in lowbie zones, etc, etc, etc.  How often would phinny be camped if not for the epics.  How often would uber guilds be in Hate or Fear if not for the epics.  They should have put these quests in VP if they wanted them to be rare and 'epic'.  Instead, they put wandering 50+ aggro mobs in LFay????  <br>
<br>
Expansions:  Apparently, the marketing plan was to put fantastic items in the expansions so that people would want to buy them.  However, they did not then go back and revamp the drops in Mistmoore, etc.  Remember the BI Bastard Sword?  Prekunark, it was not bad.  Post kunark, would *anyone* use it????  I love the kunark expansion, but that is when they started this stuff.  That is the first time they had to deal with the raised level cap.  And it just got worse with each expansion.<br>
<br>
Alt Experience:  We will not see all the problems with this for a while.  <br>
<br>
At some point, they need to recognize a balance between maintaining the integrity ofa game that so many people love, and new content to keep people interested.  Please note, new content, not new swords of uberness.  The old adage, &quot;if it ain't broke, don't fix it&quot; comes to mind.<br>
<br>
Tarf <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showPrevMessage?topicID=22320.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showNextMessage?topicID=22320.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22320.topic&index=4><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.emailToFriend?topicID=22320.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.threadControl?topicID=22320.topic><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/dagger.jpg border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=22320.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=22320.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub35.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion">Main Lounge<option value="thesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc">News Bulletin<option value="thesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies">Trai